10:
An unoccupied storehouse... We can 
use it to stay dry. I only hope the 
owner doesn't mind.
15:
That storm came out of nowhere, 
huh? Great... My socks are already 
soaking wet.
18:
Huh... Now that I get a better look, 
there sure is a lot of junk on the 
ground.
21: Perhaps we can find a light.
23:
Oh, that'd be nice. I just wish I could 
find somewhere dry to standâ€”
40: Ahaha! Now I've gotcha, ya li'l rarity!
45:
U-unleash... me at once! 
No, get your hands... off!
48:
Ooh, and you can talk! Fascinating... 
Mind if I dissect you? Come on... just 
for a bit!
55:
Who the heck are you supposed to 
be?!
58:
Please do not dissect Light. Release 
him at once.
61:
So Light's your name, is it? Mine's 
Renoir. Nice to meetcha.
63:
And I'm not REALLY gonna dissect you. 
But can I at least poke you around for 
a bit?
72:
In any case, sorry for barging in here 
and getting your things all wet and 
dirty.
75:
No worries! As you can see, this place 
wasn't exactly in tip-top shape to 
begin with.
79:
Yeah, um... What exactly is all this stuff 
here, anyway?
84:
Heh-heh... Impressed, are you? This is 
my research lab.
88: What is it that you research here?
91:
You know... a little bit of this, a little bit 
of that. Machinery and whatnot. Right 
now I'm into energy... and biology, of 
course.
93:
Oh! And Liquid Genome tooâ€”that 
medicine that merpeople seem to 
hold in such high esteem.
95:
But nothing gets me going quite like 
a real, living organism!
103:
Oh, would you look at that? The rain's 
passed. It was lovely meeting you, but 
we really should be going! Thank you 
for the hospitality. Farewell.
106:
Aww, leaving already? 
How about if I come along with you?
114:
You're all travelers, right? 
I mean, you don't look like you're from 
around here.
116:
And Light... I'd wager that you were 
human at one point, weren'tcha? It's 
all too fascinating for me to ignore!
121:
N-no... There's nothing remotely 
fascinating about me! I'm just an 
commonplace-speaking rabbit like 
any other, see?
127: Hey, all right. Calm down, buddy.
132: We'd love to have you, Renoir.
143:
Hehe... Thanks! Oh, I just can't WAIT to 
do more research on you!
